Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

- Merged 225 Zed crates into workspace (zed-upstream/crates/*)
- Added [workspace.dependencies] for all Zed internal crates (paths prefixed zed-upstream/)
- Merged external deps: superset of features, Zed's patch.crates-io
- Added Zed dev profile settings (split-debuginfo, codegen-units)
- Created .cargo/config.toml (symbol-mangling-version=v0, tokio_unstable, MACOSX_DEPLOYMENT_TARGET)

Fixes needed for cargo check -p zed:
- async-tungstenite: 0.31.0 → 0.33.0 (version conflict with jupyter-websocket-client 1.1.0)
- repl/remote_kernels.rs: add missing protocol_mode field to JupyterWebSocket literal

cargo check -p zed   ✓ (deprecation warnings only)
cargo check -p prism ✓ (pre-existing dead_code warnings only)

Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 zed-upstream/crates/repl/src/kernels/remote_kernels.rs | 5 ++++-
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/zed-upstream/crates/repl/src/kernels/remote_kernels.rs b/zed-upstream/crates/repl/src/kernels/remote_kernels.rs
index 8315f95..59afc13 100644
--- a/zed-upstream/crates/repl/src/kernels/remote_kernels.rs
+++ b/zed-upstream/crates/repl/src/kernels/remote_kernels.rs
@@ -173,7 +173,10 @@ impl RemoteRunningKernel {
 
             let (ws_stream, _response) = response?;
 
-            let kernel_socket = JupyterWebSocket { inner: ws_stream };
+            let kernel_socket = JupyterWebSocket {
+                inner: ws_stream,
+                protocol_mode: Default::default(),
+            };
 
             let (mut w, mut r): (JupyterWebSocketWriter, JupyterWebSocketReader) =
                 kernel_socket.split();
